  "writeup": "The biggest story out of Buffalo on June 24 is the official ribbon-cutting ceremony at the brand-new Highmark Stadium, with players, legends, and dignitaries celebrating the milestone moment. Quarterback Josh Allen took the opportunity to speak publicly about his lofty expectations for the 2026 season, while Hall of Famer Jim Kelly delivered an emotional appearance after revealing he recently suffered a stroke. On the roster front, pass-rusher Joey Bosa is reportedly likely done with football entirely, adding another question mark to a defensive unit already scrutinized as a potential weakness. Meanwhile, wide receiver Keon Coleman finds himself on the roster bubble, and the Bills are reportedly closing in on a contract extension with offensive lineman O'Cyrus Torrence to protect their franchise quarterback.",
